# Core Project Conventions

## Forbidden Paths and Files
- DO NOT edit generated or dependency artifacts:
  - node_modules/**
  - .next/**
  - build/**
  - dist/**
  - **/*.lock
  - package-lock.json
  - yarn.lock
  - pnpm-lock.yaml

- DO NOT edit lines ending with // IMPORTANT
- DO NOT edit code inside /* IMPORTANT */ comment blocks
- DO NOT commit secrets or environment files:
  - .env
  - .env.*
  - env/*.env
  - secrets/**

## Package Management
- Use only yarn for package management
- Avoid npm/pnpm/bun commands in scripts/documentation
- Examples: yarn, yarn add <pkg>, yarn add -D <pkg>

## Allowed Exceptions
- Modification is allowed if explicit override marker is present: // AI:ALLOW_MODIFY

## Linting and Formatting
- Keep ESLint clean in CI
- Use Prettier formatting
- Import order: builtin, external, internal (separate groups with blank line)

## Comments
- Avoid obvious/redundant comments that restate the code
- Prefer comments that explain 'why', not 'what'
- Examples:
  - Bad: const count = count + 1; // Bad: increments count
  - Good: // Good: Using +1 to avoid off-by-one when moving to the next page in pagination